article.headline: Binghamton 91, Long Island U. 80
article.story: VESTAL, N.Y. (AP) -- Richard Forbes and Troy Hailey each scored 19 points to lead Binghamton to a 91-80 come-from-behind win over Long Island Friday night. Steve Proctor added 17 points for Binghamton (4-4), which shot 47.4 percent from the field. The Bearcats snapped a three-game losing streak with the win. Long Island (4-7) was ahead 41-29 at the end of the first half. But the Bearcats rallied late in the second half when Forbes scored eight consecutive points to give Binghamton the lead for good. James Williams had 22 points for the Blackbirds and Jaytornah Wisseh added 18. Long Island shot 48 percent from the field.
